          "type": "text",
          "text": "Implement Supabase integration in services/supabase_client.py.\n\nRequirements:\n- Use a single Supabase connection string from an environment variable called SUPABASE_CONNECTION_STRING.\n- Do not use separate SUPABASE_URL or SUPABASE_KEY variables.\n- Connect to Supabase using this single connection string.\n\nCreate a function to store simulation history in a table called \"simulations\" with the following fields:\n- id\n- angle\n- velocity\n- gravity\n- created_at\n\nBehavior:\n1. If the SUPABASE_CONNECTION_STRING environment variable is missing, print a clear message:\n\n\"Supabase connection string not found. Please add SUPABASE_CONNECTION_STRING in the .env file.\"\n\n2. The function should be able to insert a simulation record into the database.\n\nExample .env configuration:\n\nREDACTED ",
